{%- comment -%}
  b2b-collection-filter.liquid — Collection-listing recipe

  We can't intercept Shopify's Search & Discovery collection results
  server-side from a theme app extension. This snippet ships a CSS fallback
  that hides product cards carrying the data-b2b-only="true" attribute when
  the visitor is not a B2B customer. Merchants are also instructed (in
  MANUAL_STEPS.md "Phase 1B") to add a Search & Discovery metafield filter
  rule excluding b2b.b2b_only == true from collection results — that filter
  is the primary defence; this CSS is belt-and-braces for themes that don't
  honour the filter.

  Usage: render in theme.liquid's <head> (or wherever global CSS is included).
  Theme integrators wire each collection-card to set data-b2b-only="..." from
  the per-product metafield.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign customer_is_b2b = false -%}
{%- if customer and customer.b2b? -%}
  {%- assign customer_is_b2b = true -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- unless customer_is_b2b -%}
  <style>
    [data-b2b-only="true"] { display: none !important; }
  </style>
{%- endunless -%}
